at a restaurant

32:14.190 --> 32:16.129
for as long as I can remember.

32:16.130 --> 32:16.963
When I was a kid,

32:16.964 --> 32:18.399
I worked for the neighborhood
diner washing dishes.

32:18.400 --> 32:21.089
I worked my way through
college serving tables.

32:21.090 --> 32:22.169
Fast forward to now,

32:22.170 --> 32:25.039
and I am the general
manager of a four-star,

32:25.040 --> 32:28.199
chef-driven, fine-dining
establishment,

32:28.200 --> 32:30.249
serving some of the
best food in town.

32:30.250 --> 32:32.409
Well, you seem to
enjoy working there.

32:32.410 --> 32:35.459
It's a great job,
pay's not bad either.

32:35.460 --> 32:36.293
But to be honest,

32:36.294 --> 32:37.859
the best reward is getting
to work with someone

32:37.860 --> 32:40.579
that's the caliber
of Chef John Lando.

32:40.580 --> 32:44.099
The food, the food is killer,

32:44.100 --> 32:46.139
especially in the last
couple of months.

32:46.140 --> 32:47.869
And you know me, I like trying
new recipes, I like to cook,

32:47.870 --> 32:49.719
but if I've got Chef John

32:49.720 --> 32:51.089
cooking for me, why bother?

32:51.090 --> 32:53.339
You're lucky to be
doing what you love.

32:53.340 --> 32:56.859
I've never met anyone who's
as much into food as you are.

32:56.860 --> 32:57.963
I can't help it!

32:58.981 --> 33:00.149
You know, lately, I've been
reading more cookbooks

33:00.150 --> 33:01.764
than I have fiction

33:01.765 --> 33:04.803
and watching more Food
Network than I have films.

33:06.067 --> 33:08.484
