The Japanese believed they can
flavor this exclusive meat

42:32.530 --> 42:35.849
with extensive care
and attention.

42:35.850 --> 42:38.349
Not only do they
control their diet,

42:38.350 --> 42:42.389
but they can feed the
cows beer and sake.

42:42.390 --> 42:45.139
And they massage the cows, dude.

42:45.140 --> 42:46.153
What a way to go.

42:47.320 --> 42:50.389
The flavors in this
dish are so compelling.

42:50.390 --> 42:52.859
I wish I could take a
photograph for my blog.

42:52.860 --> 42:54.069
No photos!

42:54.070 --> 42:57.643
I know, I just wish I could.

43:00.163 --> 43:02.319
Wait till you try
the next course.

43:02.320 --> 43:03.220
Kidney.

43:03.221 --> 43:04.719
Oh, how are you
cooking the kidney?

43:04.720 --> 43:08.069
Oh, kidney is a fun little dish.

43:08.070 --> 43:11.409
First, you gotta get in and
pull off the membrane,

43:11.410 --> 43:12.243
but you're gonna need to leave

43:12.244 --> 43:14.499
a little fat on there
for flavor, you know.

43:14.500 --> 43:17.149
Now, most people'll tell ya
that you gotta marinate it

43:17.150 --> 43:18.979
with a little vinegar
and soy sauce

43:18.980 --> 43:21.219
because it's a
pretty stinky organ,

43:21.220 --> 43:24.199
but I like to add just a
little bit of milk in there

43:24.200 --> 43:25.983
to cut right through the flavor.

43:27.060 --> 43:30.539
Then, a little garlic,
a little onion,

43:30.540 --> 43:33.289
and we dice that kidney up
into little half inchers

43:33.290 --> 43:35.839
and drop it in, a little simmer.

43:35.840 --> 43:39.463
Add some aromatics like a
bonyato or some carrots.

43:45.200 --> 43:46.809
What's wrong, Mueller?

43:46.810 --> 43:49.183
Little awful talk
makin' ya uneasy?

43:50.150 --> 43:52.429
That's the problem
with most Americans.

43:52.430 --> 43:54.249
They don't respect the awful.

43:54.250 --> 43:57.607
No one seems to realize that
tenderloins are finite.

43:59.957 --> 44:02.739
I'm sorry, I got dizzy
all of a sudden.

44:02.740 --> 44:05.957
You don't have a shellfish
or peanut allergy, do you?

44:07.047 --> 44:08.449
Uh, not that I know of.

44:08.450 --> 44:10.459
If I had a shellfish allergy,

44:10.460 --> 44:11.909
I'd just have to kill myself.

44:11.910 --> 44:13.159
Me too.

44:13.160 --> 44:15.769
My all-time favorite
wine is Vermentino,

44:15.770 --> 44:18.819
especially the later
Sardinian vintages.

44:18.820 --> 44:21.161
I can't fathom not
enjoying shrimp.

44:23.048 --> 44:24.168
What's the matter, buddy?

44:24.885 --> 44:26.839
You don't look so good.

44:26.840 --> 44:28.759
I'm sorry, everyone.

44:28.760 --> 44:31.319
I think the bubbles
from that champagne

44:31.320 --> 44:32.969
are going to my head.

44:32.970 --> 44:34.139
It's not champagne

44:34.140 --> 44:36.749
unless it comes from
the region in France.

44:36.750 --> 44:39.343
What you had was a Spanish Cava.

44:42.613 --> 44:45.449
Uh, Mr. Mueller, would
you like to lie down?

44:45.450 --> 44:48.779
I have a little room just to
the right of the kitchen,

44:48.780 --> 44:49.907
if you like.

45:00.870 --> 45:04.077
Hey buddy, how you doin'?

45:04.976 --> 45:05.976
You did all right.

45:06.860 --> 45:09.163
Chef, what's going on?

45:10.890 --> 45:12.539
Why am I in this tub?

45:12.540 --> 45:14.409
Hang in there, buddy.

45:14.410 --> 45:17.179
You just got a little
ill at dinner.

45:17.180 --> 45:19.080
You just need to rest
up a little bit.

45:22.380 --> 45:23.899
Chef, Chef, get me outta here.

45:23.900 --> 45:25.863
It's frickin' freezing in here.

45:27.220 --> 45:28.676
We'll get ya out
in a little bit.

45:28.677 --> 45:30.333
You just need to relax.

45:31.280 --> 45:33.630
You don't wanna injure
yourself anymore, do ya?

45:43.588 --> 45:45.671
I'm bleeding.

45:46.560 --> 45:48.103
Chef, why am I bleeding?

45:49.540 --> 45:52.963
Chef, what am I doing in
this tub with all this ice?

45:56.400 --> 45:57.873
What, what are you doing?

45:58.970 --> 46:02.219
French Milt said if that guy
keeps freaking out like that,

46:02.220 --> 46:04.269
he's gonna pump adrenaline
through his body,

46:04.270 --> 46:06.399
and I don't want him
spoiling those ribs

46:06.400 --> 46:07.729
before I have a chance to show

46:07.730 --> 46:10.259
the impressive pairing
I have for them.

46:10.260 --> 46:11.409
Rose, buddy.

46:11.410 --> 46:14.349
Not in the neck, you idiot.

46:14.350 --> 46:17.679
You think tasting the adrenaline
and the endorphins are bad?

46:17.680 --> 46:19.039
Once those drugs hit his system,

46:19.040 --> 46:21.519
we'll be tasting
chemicals all night.

46:21.520 --> 46:22.353
You have any idea

46:22.354 --> 46:24.893
what I've been feeding
this guy for a week?

46:37.231 --> 46:39.069
Please, somebody help me!

46:39.070 --> 46:40.716
That would be the dinner bell.

46:54.133 --> 46:58.429
Mm, Brandon, these black beans
are a wonderful addition.

46:58.430 --> 47:00.849
The thigh really is
more marbled, Milt.

47:00.850 --> 47:02.519
You were right.

47:02.520 --> 47:04.543
I like the skin, crispy.

47:06.710 --> 47:08.423
Where are the skins?

47:09.570 --> 47:11.389
Oh, don't worry, pal.

47:11.390 --> 47:13.819
I'll get ya some skins
for your doggie bag.

47:13.820 --> 47:15.809
We'll have to process him
before the night's over,

47:15.810 --> 47:18.839
so they'll be plenty
of stuff for everybody

47:18.840 --> 47:21.019
for late night snackin'.

47:21.020 --> 47:22.269
Bully's picked on me in school.

47:22.270 --> 47:23.703
I never really fit in.

47:25.370 --> 47:30.233
I admit I thought about suicide
for a long, long time,

47:31.693 --> 47:36.210
but that's when I found food,
and I finally belonged,

47:37.564 --> 47:39.619
and I started the blog,
and it was like,

47:39.620 --> 47:44.369
for the first time, food
gave my life meaning.

47:44.370 --> 47:47.373
He may have been a little
old for my tastes.

47:48.590 --> 47:52.910
Think about it, nobody eats a
farm animal in its late 20s.

47:52.911 --> 47:53.919
Yeah, that's why your work

47:53.920 --> 47:56.453
with molecular gastronomy
is so amazing.

47:57.760 --> 47:59.410
It's not tough or
stringy at all.

48:00.580 --> 48:03.949
So, what's the next course?

48:03.950 --> 48:06.099
It's something to know

48:06.100 --> 48:08.889
I can look back on those
bullies back in school

48:08.890 --> 48:11.589
and know that they know nothing

48:11.590 --> 48:14.894
about the difference between
cured ham and prosciutto.

48:15.729 --> 48:19.039
Savages know nothing
of sous vide, right?

48:19.040 --> 48:22.333
Enjoy your white
zinfandel, peons.

48:26.540 --> 48:27.740
Check his temperature.

48:29.200 --> 48:30.450
Don't hit the bone, dude.

48:31.400 --> 48:32.400
I know.

48:38.383 --> 48:40.782
Teddy, Teddy, what's going on?

48:40.783 --> 48:42.409
Calm down.

48:42.410 --> 48:46.142
Oh my god, is that
meat thermometer?

48:49.039 --> 48:50.734
Please, don't do this, please!

48:50.735 --> 48:52.382
Please, don't do this!

48:52.383 --> 48:53.703
He's still squealing in here?

48:55.000 --> 48:56.084
Check these out.

48:56.085 --> 48:56.950
They come up in New York.

48:56.951 --> 48:58.279
This one's for power.

48:58.280 --> 48:59.430
This one's for finesse.

49:02.379 --> 49:04.632
Plus, they cut
through bone, dude.

49:11.546 --> 49:13.463
No, no, no!

49:16.780 --> 49:19.763
Hold still or it's gonna
hurt a whole lot worse!

49:25.998 --> 49:27.579
You better get a
rollin' pin in here.

49:27.580 --> 49:29.899
We gotta shut this guy up!

49:29.900 --> 49:32.469
John: I'll take care
of this, French Milt.

49:32.470 --> 49:34.453
Relax, and wrap those
fingers in bacon.

49:36.150 --> 49:37.705
Remember, there's eight of us,

49:37.706 --> 49:40.006
and we need all of his
fingers, and no thumbs.

49:41.301 --> 49:42.634
Those are nasty.

49:50.539 --> 49:52.689
I was gonna make a little
pate out of these guys,

49:52.690 --> 49:54.663
but they went a different route.

49:55.710 --> 49:57.409
Personally, I think
whole sous vide thing

49:57.410 --> 50:02.001
is a passing phase and
overrated, but when in Rome.

50:14.185 --> 50:17.049
Wow, I don't think we're
topping that thigh.

50:17.050 --> 50:20.079
Hey, anybody want a Pimm's?

50:20.080 --> 50:21.699
Oh, I just adore Pimm's.

50:21.700 --> 50:22.700
I'll have some.

50:22.701 --> 50:24.599
Don't even think of
ruining your palate

50:24.600 --> 50:26.099
with those botanicals.

50:26.100 --> 50:27.739
The juniper in that liquor

50:27.740 --> 50:30.019
will counteract the
delicate tannins

50:30.020 --> 50:32.509
and soft finish of the
Burgundy I've selected.

50:32.510 --> 50:34.469
Oh, but this is gin-based.

50:34.470 --> 50:36.759
I've got the Pimm's
number six up.

50:36.760 --> 50:37.899
It's vodka.

50:37.900 --> 50:39.579
I thought they stopped
making that years ago.

50:39.580 --> 50:40.580
They did.

51:18.330 --> 51:20.079
So, tell me, Brandon,

51:20.080 --> 51:23.339
what inspired genius we'll be
enjoying in the next course.

51:23.340 --> 51:25.409
Ah, it's a little something

51:25.410 --> 51:28.709
French Milt and John,
they dream up.

51:28.710 --> 51:32.319
We take the fingers,
we wrap them in bacon,

51:32.320 --> 51:35.869
and serve them over
white bean cassoulet.

51:35.870 --> 51:38.693
The white beans are from
the farmer's market.

51:38.694 --> 51:39.694
Oh.

51:40.441 --> 51:42.319
Still think it's
fundamentally wrong

51:42.320 --> 51:43.409
that we're keepin' him alive.

51:43.410 --> 51:45.279
I mean, really, it is not right.

51:45.280 --> 51:47.189
You're being ridiculous.

51:47.190 --> 51:48.372
Am I really?

51:48.373 --> 51:50.889
It is a proven fact
that the hogfish,

51:50.890 --> 51:54.119
which is headshot in the
Keys, dies more quickly,

51:54.120 --> 51:56.249
so heart stops pumpin'
blood to the organs,

51:56.250 --> 51:58.189
which, in turn,
preserves the meat.

51:58.190 --> 52:01.713
The fish never goes into
shock, mean never gets sour.

52:50.010 --> 52:51.999
Ancient cultures
have long believed

52:52.000 --> 52:54.079
that fear seasons the kill.

52:54.080 --> 52:56.439
Fear and maybe a little
bit of bacon fat.

52:56.440 --> 52:58.499
Everything tastes
better with bacon.

52:58.500 --> 53:02.063
I prefer to do my flavorings
with my meat myself.

53:11.970 --> 53:14.060
So Brandon, how does he taste?

53:15.266 --> 53:16.266
Hannah?

53:18.418 --> 53:20.049
You're a part of this?

53:20.050 --> 53:21.153
Shit!

53:26.603 --> 53:28.769
I actually googled Donner party

53:28.770 --> 53:29.770
cookin' methods the other day.

53:29.771 --> 53:31.969
I musta looked at 100
different sites.

53:31.970 --> 53:33.869
And there was this
very droll documentary

53:33.870 --> 53:35.899
about the whole affair,
which I have to say,

53:35.900 --> 53:38.269
conveniently left out how
they prepared the food.

53:38.270 --> 53:40.779
Oh, that's ridiculous.

53:40.780 --> 53:43.219
Those who don't learn about
mistakes in the past

53:43.220 --> 53:45.159
are condemned to repeat them.

53:45.160 --> 53:47.299
That's what they say.

53:47.300 --> 53:49.190
Or something like that anyway.

53:50.287 --> 53:53.119
The only thing I did find
was one word, roasted,

53:53.120 --> 53:54.439
which could mean anything.

53:54.440 --> 53:55.849
I mean, how did they roast it?

53:55.850 --> 53:58.049
Did they use wood like in
a traditional barbecue,

53:58.050 --> 54:02.842
and if so, what kinda wood,
hickory, oak, larch?

54:02.843 --> 54:04.793
I think they used
mesquite out West.

54:24.510 --> 54:26.177
Stop your whining.

54:33.262 --> 54:34.262
Greg.

54:35.086 --> 54:38.699
Greg?

54:38.700 --> 54:39.700
Greg?

54:46.520 --> 54:48.547
Now, it's my pleasure
to serve you.

55:06.610 --> 55:09.519
Where do you think
you're going, Mueller?

55:09.520 --> 55:10.718
Look at you.

55:10.719 --> 55:15.139
Tch, tch, tch, you won't make
it a block in your condition,

55:15.140 --> 55:17.079
not unless you let me help you.

55:17.080 --> 55:18.183
It's cold out there.

55:20.790 --> 55:23.129
Give us the bottle, Mueller.

55:23.130 --> 55:26.399
Stop being such a
naughty boy, Mueller.

55:26.400 --> 55:28.919
You know you don't
wanna hurt us.

55:28.920 --> 55:30.679
If you put that bottle down,

55:30.680 --> 55:34.053
I promise I'll give you the
spanking of your life.

55:35.900 --> 55:37.773
You know you wanna
give it to me.

55:40.350 --> 55:42.727
I like my wine full bodied.

56:06.890 --> 56:10.449
I am sick and tired

56:10.450 --> 56:13.693
of being the one getting cut on.

56:14.990 --> 56:17.471
I'm gonna kill everyone
of you sick mother...

56:29.200 --> 56:30.652
Hannah.

56:33.820 --> 56:35.683
You little food whore.

56:39.680 --> 56:42.539
You guys owe me big
time for this one.

56:42.540 --> 56:45.209
I was just supposed
to seduce the prey.

56:45.210 --> 56:47.503
It was your job
to make the kill.

56:48.860 --> 56:51.063
Oh well, the things I
do for a good meal.

56:53.970 --> 56:55.083
Nice shot, Hannah.

56:57.330 --> 56:58.919
See what I was
tellin' ya, Brandon?

56:58.920 --> 57:01.739
Instant kill stops the heart,
meat doesn't go into shock.

57:01.740 --> 57:04.259
I still think there are
exquisite flavors you get

57:04.260 --> 57:06.469
when blood pump
through the heart,

57:06.470 --> 57:09.349
especially the fearful heart.

57:09.350 --> 57:11.619
You remember pig
we have last week.

57:11.620 --> 57:12.770
Oh, you mean the cop?

57:15.150 --> 57:17.829
What do we do about
all these bodies?

57:17.830 --> 57:20.179
That's a whole lot of meat.

57:20.180 --> 57:22.329
I have a very big deep freezer.

57:22.330 --> 57:24.680
Let's chunk these bodies
up and get 'em on ice.

57:26.090 --> 57:27.640
Let's get this heart out quick.

57:47.341 --> 57:50.220
♪ You and me alone ♪

57:50.221 --> 57:52.972
♪ With a hunger and a craving ♪

58:14.670 --> 58:15.670
You're late.

58:19.640 --> 58:22.083
Last minute red tape,
but we're here.

58:23.060 --> 58:24.060
Burton.

58:26.000 --> 58:27.600
Can you please open this, sir?

58:28.690 --> 58:31.029
There's no need to call me sir.

58:32.615 --> 58:36.370
My friends call me Snake,
you know, like Plissken.

58:49.570 --> 58:50.570
It's clear.

59:06.350 --> 59:07.400
Keep movin', idiot.

59:22.729 --> 59:24.109
Are you ready for this last step

59:24.110 --> 59:26.007
in your recovery program, R.J.?

59:30.200 --> 59:32.113
And why are we doing this?

59:33.290 --> 59:36.969
I have to know,
once and for all,

59:36.970 --> 59:40.173
that what I saw that
night wasn't real,

59:41.250 --> 59:46.250
that it was just a figment of
my overactive imagination.

59:47.350 --> 59:48.679
Good.

59:48.680 --> 59:50.709
The sooner you can accept that,

59:50.710 --> 59:52.843
the sooner you can move
on with your life.

59:59.410 --> 01:00:00.410
Good luck, kid.

01:00:01.522 --> 01:00:02.939
Thanks, Burton.

01:00:38.693 --> 01:00:41.009
We'll give him 10 minutes.

01:00:41.010 --> 01:00:44.181
So, what happened in there
that made him go all nutso?

01:00:44.182 --> 01:00:46.382
Seven years ago, his
brother went missing.

01:00:47.940 --> 01:00:50.613
R.J. was babysitting
him at the time.

01:01:16.040 --> 01:01:19.179
He went looking for his
sibling all around the house

01:01:19.180 --> 01:01:21.799
and later found him
dead in the basement.

01:01:21.800 --> 01:01:24.543
He suffered a total mental
breakdown from the trauma.

01:01:42.641 --> 01:01:44.809
He went into a catatonic state,

01:01:44.810 --> 01:01:47.329
didn't talk or
communicate for a year.

01:01:47.330 --> 01:01:49.979
He blamed himself for
his brother's death.

01:01:49.980 --> 01:01:51.423
How'd his brother die?

01:01:52.830 --> 01:01:53.833
He bled to death.

01:01:54.750 --> 01:01:56.033
Somebody stabbed him?

01:01:57.200 --> 01:01:59.943
Actually, someone cut
his genitals off.

01:02:00.980 --> 01:02:01.910
Poor kid.

01:02:01.911 --> 01:02:06.379
By the way, they never did
find his you know what.

01:02:06.380 --> 01:02:08.049
Or the person who did it,

01:02:08.050 --> 01:02:10.073
which only added to
R.J.'s paranoia.

01:02:11.290 --> 01:02:13.069
His religious parents
had warned him

01:02:13.070 --> 01:02:14.859
about playing with himself.

01:02:14.860 --> 01:02:16.579
Masturbation was the
most sinful thing

01:02:16.580 --> 01:02:17.769
you could do in that household,

01:02:17.770 --> 01:02:20.779
and if you gave into
such devilish behavior,

01:02:20.780 --> 01:02:22.523
the knob goblin would get you.

01:02:42.401 --> 01:02:44.059
All right, you bastard.

01:02:44.060 --> 01:02:47.422
If you're real, show yourself.

01:03:06.040 --> 01:03:08.899
We may never know who
actually killed his brother,

01:03:08.900 --> 01:03:11.509
but at least we can get some
closure for R.J.'s psyche.

01:03:11.510 --> 01:03:13.409
The last step is acknowledging

01:03:13.410 --> 01:03:18.410
there's no such thing as demonic
creatures in the basement.

01:03:42.900 --> 01:03:44.283
Time's up R.J.

01:03:46.280 --> 01:03:47.757
Did you hear me, R.J.?

01:03:59.440 --> 01:04:00.440
Well, shit.

01:04:09.850 --> 01:04:11.150
What the hell you doin'?

01:04:12.332 --> 01:04:13.332
Call the police.

01:04:16.990 --> 01:04:20.267
So, I still get paid
for this, right?

